column5: Jr. and I headed down to West lake Willows for a couple days of fishing.Had a great time as usual.A ton of Oos fish but thats just the way it goes..Ended up with 5 pike ,18 Crappie,33 oos largies and endless rock bass.Oh and a half dozen perch.
Guess I can only speak for myself but if I tied into that many out of season fish I'd move!
Wow...seems like the crappie are really taking off in West Lake...too bad you didn't tie into any walleye...sounds like you had fun though

Its not like we were targeting the oos fish.Every oos fish caught was released.I don't take my son out of school for 2 days to teach him that.We never anchored once,it just so happened that targeting pike and walleye, they(oos fish) seemed to be every where.All over Westlake.

oh man, I wish my dad had taken me out of school to go fishing. Actually, my dad wasn't a fisherman, so we didn't go fishing school or no school! Is this west Lake with the sand dunes? I used to fish there many years ago...and if they had a few more musky in there I'd probably go back some day
Sounds like lots of action junior must have been pleased.
Is this west Lake with the sand dunes? I used to fish there many years ago...and if they had a few more musky in there I'd probably go back some day      yep, same lake
glad to hear things are still good out that way. I remember fishing east lake as well...was like shooting fish in a barrel some days
